Basic HTML Format:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Testing</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello Vijay</h1>
     
 
<p>My first Website</p>
 
 
</body>
</html>


How to link the css file in HTML: <link rel="stylesheet" href="mystyle.css">
There are three ways of inserting a style sheet:

External CSS: c	ss things is updated to style.css file. That is called as external css

Internal CSS:
<head>
<style>
<h1>{
color: yellow;
</h1>
</style>
</head>

Inline CSS -> Directly in the HTML element <p>: <h1 style="color:red">Welcome</h1>

